laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is enlarged, with hyperemia and wall thickening, measuring up to 11 mm. There is extensive surrounding phlegmonous changes with a 1.6 cm rounded hypodense area with peripheral enhancement adjacent to the appendiceal tip concerning for a small abscess. There is also a small amount of free fluid in the pelvis surrounding the inflamed appendix.
